  "texts": [
    "According to Mnih et al. (2015), all DQN-based methods (some of the most relevant are presented in Sect. 4) used a fixed replay memory size of 1 M transitions.",
    "Recently, some research works investigated the effects of small and large buffers (Zhang and Sutton 2017; Liu and Zou 2018).",
    "In turn, Neves et al. (2022) used a small dynamic memory to explore the replay of the experience and the dynamics of the transitions, reducing the number of experiences required for agent learning.",
    "Looking at the history of reinforcement learning, some of the most recent and significant improvements have arisen from the possibility of approximating value functions from multidimensional data.",
    "At this point, adopting artificial neural networks was a promising proposition deeply investigated in the early related literature, including Lin (1992)."
  ],
